This is a mirror of http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=4273

If a current file looks like an executable script,
make it by executable running "chmod +x %".

Requirements:
- Vim 7.2 or later

Latest version:
http://github.com/tyru/autochmodx.vim

Latest document:
https://github.com/tyru/autochmodx.vim/blob/master/doc/autochmodx.txt

Latest document with syntax highlight:
http://vim-doc.heroku.com/view?https://raw.github.com/tyru/autochmodx.vim/master/doc/autochmodx.txt
